race.comment: FRANCE'S BOY (2) is a stalwart of the SA ranks, at start 162 and is going just as good as ever. Doesn't know how to run a bad one and is sure to be giving himself every chance again up on speed. Was a winner over this track and trip when last here back in October. Can repeat the dose. DORA AURORA (5) broke through stylishly when resuming at Clare. Was poor two back but bounced back sharply last time at Mt Gambier. Peak fitness now and is drawn to get all the favours. DRAGONFACE (7) progressed nicely here at the latest when closing off strongly again into the placings. Hasn't won for a long time but is building towards one. NIGHT CRUISER (9) gave a bold sight last time in town, only to be collared late. Can be a touch more conservative this time. In the mix. UNWIND (8) is fitter and can make her presence felt from the good draw.
